My name is Dan Knight,yesterday I was not as wise as today and THANK GOD for the possibility of gaining more wisdom Tomorrow,I remember about being in Vietnam 1966-1972 and also about experiencing more fear about the return home,never thought it would take so long,sure didn't take that long to get there.I think I should be honest,I still feel that my journey is still in progress,perhaps contributing to this journal will help me and hopefully another,seem's like many of us have allowed the feeling's of others become a catalyst for paving a road to places better put into light than born into darkness,often we place in front of us a sign that says&quot;BEWARE&quot; of what?That we hurt,we have fear,we want to feel,I was in the 196th. Lt.Inf.Bde.Co.B4th.Bn.31st.Infantry/175th.Avn.&quot;OUTLAW'S Vinh Long,doesn't make me a better person than someone else,agent orange followed me here and I have terminal cancer,doesn't stop me,my Wife and I are building a Swimming pool&quot;nice big one too&quot;=Have Children&amp;Grandchildren will swim,life is somewhere between where I /WE are and what we are willing to risk to get to where we atleast think we want to be,you out there may believe me to be short a few brick's,this is true,you see they are in the flower garden,where a child may see them.Vietnam was not a bad place,Vietnamese were/nor are now bad people,we soldier's were sent to help and it was not we who had control of the helm,the people who protested the war effort's were doing so because they&quot;Felt&quot;they were doing what was right,WE THE PEOPLE AS A WHOLE must work through our differences so that WE may present to those who come after us a presence of togatherness combined with a willingness to admit that there are many paths to Tomorrow,and may those who come be willing to take the risk of being sometimes wrong to protect those things which are most sacred,LIFE,LIBERTY,FREEDOM,Thank You and may this vehicle alway's be one that respects the WISDOM OF THE TRUTH!!!
